
1. What is the difference between st.title() and st.header()?

st.title() creates largest, boldest heading (app main title). st.header() is slightly smaller for section titles.

| Function                | Size         | Use Case      |
| ----------------------- | ------------ | ------------- |
| st.title("Dashboard")   | Largest      | App name      |
| st.header("Sales Data") | Medium-large | Page sections |

st.title("🚀 Sales Dashboard")    # Top of app
st.header("📊 Monthly Report")     # Section header



2. How can you create custom-size headings using Markdown?

Use # symbols in st.markdown():

python
st.markdown("# H1 - Largest")      # Title size
st.markdown("## H2 - Header size") 
st.markdown("### H3 - Subheader")
st.markdown("#### H4 - Smaller")

Full control:

python
st.markdown("""
# 🎯 Main Title
## 📈 Section 1
### 📋 Sub-section
""")



3. Why are headings important in a Streamlit app?

Structure + Navigation for users:

    Visual hierarchy (scan page quickly)

    Section separation (data vs charts vs controls)

    Professional look (not wall of text)

    Mobile friendly (clear sections)

text
No headings = 📄 Wall of text
With headings = 📋 Organized dashboard



4. How does st.subheader() help in structuring an app?

subheader() creates third-level headings for sub-sections within headers:

python
st.title("Sales Dashboard")
st.header("2026 Data")
st.subheader("Q1 Results")    # Under 2026 Data
st.line_chart(q1_data)

st.subheader("Q2 Results")    # Same level
st.line_chart(q2_data)

Perfect for: Grouping related charts/controls.



5. Can we mix Markdown and Streamlit functions for headings? Explain.

YES - combine freely for perfect control:

python
# Streamlit functions
st.title("🏢 Company Dashboard")
st.header("📈 Revenue")
st.subheader("Monthly Breakdown")

# Markdown for custom
st.markdown("### 💰 Profit Margin")
st.markdown("#### 📊 By Product")

# Mix in same section
st.header("Charts")
st.markdown("## **Interactive Widgets**")

Pro tip: Use st.title() once at top, then mix st.header() + markdown for sections.

Headings = Professional dashboard structure! 🎯📋
